    "created_at": "2016-06-07T06:06:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-07T06:06:50Z",
    "body": "After looking into this again, I think it is better not to support `~` in file dialogs. The `~` is a shell feature, and also a valid character for filenames, supporting it will make our API have unexpected behaviors when users do want to use `~` as a filename. \n"
